This paper is primarily focused on the problem of Inverse Reinforcement Learning (IRL), which is a subfield of Machine Learning (ML) and Artificial Intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the application of the proposed method to autonomous robot cars, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of demonstrations generated by humans/experts, which is related to Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper uses Expectation-Maximization formulation and non-parametric clustering, which are related to Systems and Control (cs.SY).
